Package model

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Agent
    Interface for active model objects.
    CarAcceptor
    An interface for all Objects that can accept Car objects.
    TimeServer
    An interface class that works as a way of running Agent Objects over a set span of time.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Car
    A car remembers its position from the beginning of its road.
    CarTEST
    A test class of the Car Object class.
    ComponentFactory
    A Factory class that creates all the necessary CarAcceptor and Agent Objects for the Traffic Simulation.
    IntegrationTEST1
    An integration Test for all the model classes that have been created.
    Intersection
    The Intersection is a crossroads between to CarAcceptor Objects running North/South, and two CarAcceptor Objects running East/West.
    IntersectionTEST
    A test class for the Intersection Object class.
    Light
    A light has a LightState that determines which cars can pass through an Intersection Object.
    Model
    The model contains roads and intersections organized in a matrix.
    MP
    A singleton class that holds all of the user set parameters for the Traffic Simulator.
    MPTEST  
    Road
    A road holds cars.
    RoadTEST
    A test class for the Road Object class.
    Sink
    A sink is the end point of the last CarAcceptor.
    Source
    Creates Car Objects and places them onto the next CarAcceptor Object.
    SourceTEST  
    TimeServerQueue
    An implementation of TimeServer that uses a priority queue to decide when to run Agent Objects.
    TimeServerTEST
    A test Class for the TimeServer class.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    LightState
    The Enum class that takes care of all the possible combinations of light colors at in Intersection.
